ter Insurance\n16\t* **The Master Account:** Open a fee-free community business checking account at a local credit union using the approved MN State Articles of Incorporation and IRS EIN letter.\n17\t* **The Master Insurance Wrapper:** Secure an annual Commercial General Liability (CGL) Policy for small civic associations (target range: $600–$900/year). The policy must maintain a minimum limit of $1,000,000 per occurrence / $2,000,000 aggregate to satisfy municipal street closure mandates.\n18\t\n19\t### 4. Intellectual Property Lock\n20\tAll digital assets, bylaws, guides, and materials generated by MNeighbor Alliance are natively stamped with a Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial-ShareAlike (CC BY-NC-SA 4.0) License. This legally guarantees that anyone can copy or modify the network frameworks, but nobody can ever sell them or commercialize the ecosystem.\n21\t"}}
