[2026-07-19 18:41:35] [claude-sdk] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01UMSrKJXPxqqAdP8LTmT3ri","type":"tool_result","content":"# Lexington-Hamline Community Council: Resources Page Content\n\n## Organization Information\n**Name:** Lexington-Hamline Community Council (LHCC)\n**Address:** 1168 Selby Avenue, Saint Paul, MN 55104\n**Phone:** (763) 393-7043\n**Email:** lexham@lexham.org\n\n---\n\n## Community Resources Provided\n\n### 1. City of Saint Paul Services\nContact information and links for municipal issues:\n- **Western Police District:** 651-266-5512\n- **Citizen Service Line:** 651-266-8989\n- Incident reporting form available online\n- Recycling services information\n- City update subscription service\n- Composting/yard waste guidance\n- Neighborhood safety resources\n- Utilities information\n- Parking regulations\n- Bicycling resources\n- Walking resources\n- Scooter regulations\n\n### 2. Aging In Place Resources\nDescription: \"A person chooses to live in their home as they age, rather than moving to assisted living or nursing home.\" Local resources available with dedicated information page.\n\n### 3. Housing Resources\n- MN Housing (mnhousing.gov)\n- Tenant Rights handbook (Minnesota Attorney General)\n- Housing Counseling services locator\n- Problem Properties complaint reporting\n\n### 4. Buy Nothing Facebook Group\n\"Members share, lend, give and receive through hyper-local gift networks\" connecting real-life neighbors. Group link: facebook.com/groups/shrchlh/\n\n### 5. Lex-Ham Community Arts\nTheatre and music organization emphasizing \"traditional classics, undiscovered treasures and locally-created work.\" Website: lexhamarts.org\n\n---\n\n## Website Navigation Structure\n- About Us (Council, Board, Documents, Staff)\n- Community (Get Involved, Programs, Social Media Rules, Calendar, Merchandise, Donations)\n- Social Media: Instagram and Facebook pages linked"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"393aa5