[2026-07-19 18:42:07] [claude-sdk] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01QknTKy5ZjtahrvdQQURcX7","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"Lexington-Hamline Community Council resources community Saint Paul\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"About Us — Lexington-Hamline Community Council\",\"url\":\"https://www.lexham.org/about\"},{\"title\":\"Programs — Lexington-Hamline Community Council\",\"url\":\"https://www.lexham.org/lhccprograms\"},{\"title\":\"Donate — Lexington-Hamline Community Council\",\"url\":\"https://www.lexham.org/donate/\"},{\"title\":\"Our Store — Lexington-Hamline Community Council\",\"url\":\"https://www.lexham.org/our-store\"},{\"title\":\"Safety Links – The Lexington-Hamline Community Council\",\"url\":\"https://lexham.org/community/safety-links/\"},{\"title\":\"Home - The Lexington-Hamline Community Council\",\"url\":\"https://www.lexham.org/home\"},{\"title\":\"Merch — Lexington-Hamline Community Council\",\"url\":\"https://www.lexham.org/merch\"},{\"title\":\"Board of Directors — Lexington-Hamline Community Council\",\"url\":\"https://www.lexham.org/board\"},{\"title\":\"Auction page in development – The Lexington-Hamline Community Council\",\"url\":\"https://lexham.org/the-2020-annual-meeting-silent-auction/all-auctions/\"},{\"title\":\"Mask Drive for Skyline Tower – The Lexington-Hamline Community Council\",\"url\":\"https://lexham.org/covid-19-idea-board/mask-drive-for-skyline-tower/\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here's what I found about the Lexington-Hamline Community Council and its resources in Saint Paul:\n\n## About the Organization\n\nThe Lexington-Hamline Community Council's purpose is to improve the quality of life and bring about positive community change in the Lexington-Hamline neighborhood of St. Paul through the active involvement of neighborhood residents in community projects, programs, and direct action on issues which affect the neighborhood.\n\n## Programs & Resources\n\nThe council offers several community programs and resources:\n\n- **Community Gardens**: The organization maintains the Dunning Community Garden at the corner of Griggs Street N. and Concordia Ave., the Lex-Ham Community Garden on Marshall Ave., and the Eleanor Graham Community Garden in the triangle between Ayd Mill Road, Hamline, and Ashland.\n\n- **Welcome Program**: Welcome Wagon volunteers provide welcome gift bags for newcomers to the neighborhood.\n\n- **Community Events**: The council hosts a concert series, community conversations, Ice Cream Social, and Spaghetti Dinner, as well as providing connection between residents, businesses and the City of Saint Paul.\n\n- **Safety Resources**: The Lex-Ham Crime and Safety Committee meets on the 3rd Monday of each month at 3:30 PM at Yellowbird Coffee Bar.\n\n## Contact Information\n\nThe organization can be reached at lexham@lexham.org, 763-393-7043, or at 1168 Selby Avenue Saint Paul, MN 55104.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"393aa51d-281a-4b41-acea-1abc9b5cff0a","uuid":"fa25f975-08e9-49e7-8be8-7894bcb9072d","timestamp":"2026-07-19T23:42:07.444Z","tool_use_result":{"query":"Lexington-Hamline Community Council resources community Saint Paul","results":[{"tool_use_id":"srvtoolu_01PAcGpNKjPFMSsfiuDa58wp","content":[{"title":"About Us — Lexington-Hamline Community Council","url":"https://www.lexham.org/about"},{"title":"Programs — Lexington-Hamline Community Council","url":"https://www.lexham.org/lhccprograms"},{"title":"Donate — Lexington-Hamline Community Council","url":"https://www.lexham.org/donate/"},{"title":"Our Store — Lexington-Hamline Community Council","url":"https://www.lexham.org/our-store"},{"title":"Safety Links – The Lexington-Hamline Community Council","url":"https://lexham.org/community/safety-links/"},{"title":"Home - The Lexington-Hamline Community Council","url":"https://www