[2026-07-19 18:42:22] [claude-sdk] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01STUjfXcjpLw9PG8KS4hpTb","type":"tool_result","content":"# Lexington-Hamline Community Council Overview\n\n## Mission and Vision\n\nThe organization's purpose is to \"enhance the quality of life and foster positive change in the Lexington-Hamline neighborhood\" through resident engagement in projects and programs addressing community needs.\n\nThe council envisions \"a vibrant, inclusive, and connected Lexington-Hamline neighborhood\" where people work together to build a thriving community while celebrating diversity and tackling challenges collaboratively.\n\n## Organizational Structure\n\nThe LHCC operates as a tax-exempt, nonprofit organization established over 30 years ago by neighborhood residents. The council defines its service area boundaries and maintains formal governance through a board of directors, staff members, and community volunteers.\n\n## Key Accomplishments\n\nSince its founding, the organization has successfully addressed:\n- Transportation infrastructure (bridge work, traffic signals, pedestrian safety)\n- Public space development (the Hague-Schuneman Tot Lot recreation area)\n- Community programs (youth recreation, theater, gardening initiatives)\n- Resident communication (monthly newsletter publication)\n- Housing initiatives for lower-income residents\n\n## Contact Information\n\n**Address:** 1168 Selby Avenue, Saint Paul, MN 55104  \n**Phone:** (763) 393-7043  \n**Email:** lexham@lexham.org"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"393aa51d-281a-4b41-acea-1abc9b5cff0a","uuid":"4c9c1d7e-bd03-47bd-bd6a-4ff811697e41","timestamp":"2026-07-19T23:42:22.027Z","tool_use_result":{"bytes":994282,"code":200,"codeText":"OK","result":"# Lexington-Hamline Community Council Overview\n\n## Mission and Vision\n\nThe organization's purpose is to \"enhance the quality of life and foster positive change in the Lexington-Hamline neighborhood\" through resident engagement in projects and programs addressing community needs.\n\nThe council envisions \"a vibrant, inclusive, and connected Lexington-Hamline neighborhood\" where people work together to build a thriving community while celebrating diversity and tackling challenges collaboratively.\n\n## Organizational Structure\n\nThe LHCC operates as a tax-exempt, nonprofit organization established over 30 years ago by neighborhood residents. The council defines its service area boundaries and maintains formal governance through a board of directors, staff members, and community volunteers.\n\n## Key Accomplishments\n\nSince its founding, the organization has successfully addressed:\n- Transportation infrastructure (bridge work, traffic signals, pedestrian safety)\n- Public space development (the Hague-Schuneman Tot Lot recreation area)\n- Community programs (youth recreation, theater, gardening initiatives)\n- Resident communication (monthly newsletter publication)\n- Housing initiatives for lower-income residents\n\n## Contact Information\n\n**Address:** 1168 Selby Avenue, Saint Paul, MN 55104  \n**Phone:** (763) 393-7043  \n**Email:** lexham@lexham.org","durationMs":5268,"url":"https://www.lexham.org/about"}}
