[2026-07-19 18:43:30] [claude-sdk] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01VQstwM4kgQam2oroYvjyTQ","type":"tool_result","content":"# Lexington-Hamline Community Council Calendar Events\n\n## Upcoming Events (2026)\n\n**Under the Bridge Concert: Jacuzzi Puma**\n- Date: Wednesday, August 26, 2026\n- Time: 6:00 PM – 8:00 PM\n- Location: Hamline bridge area\n- Description: Evening music and community gathering. Family-friendly with playground access. Food trucks available. Band performs classic rock covers.\n\n**Yoga in the Park**\n- Date: Saturday, September 26, 2026\n- Time: 9:00 AM – 10:00 AM\n- Location: Midway Peace Park, 416 North Griggs Street\n- Description: \"gentle blend of somatics and yoga\" led by Ann Blackburn. Free and open to public.\n\n**Under the Bridge Concert - Stone Fruit and The Lesser Jackson**\n- Date: Saturday, September 26, 2026\n- Time: 6:00 PM – 8:00 PM\n- Location: 1328 Hague Avenue\n- Description: Two bands performing indie pop covers and soul classics. Family event with food trucks.\n\n**Ice Cream Social**\n- Date: Sunday, July 19, 2026\n- Time: 1:00 PM – 3:00 PM\n- Location: Hamline and Hague Tot Lot\n- Description: Music, water balloon toss, bingo, face painting, crafts. Suggested donations requested.\n\n**Movie in the Park**\n- Date: Friday, July 17, 2026\n- Time: 8:55 PM – 10:40 PM\n- Location: Midway Peace Park\n- Description: Disney's Coco screening. Free public event.\n\n**Ananya Dance Theatre Presents: Our Storied Love**\n- Date: Saturday, June 27, 2026\n- Time: 4:00 PM – 6:00 PM\n- Location: Midway Peace Park\n- Description: Dance, song, and movement for community peace and joy.\n\n**Under the Bridge Concert - Loon Voodoo**\n- Date: Friday, June 26, 2026\n- Time: 6:00 PM – 8:00 PM\n- Location: Hamline/Hague Tot Lot\n- Description: Rock band performing familiar songs from multiple decades.\n\n**Spring Scavenger Hunt**\n- Date: Saturday, May 16, 2026\n- Time: 9:00 AM – 11:00 AM\n- Location: Tot Lot