[2026-07-19 18:44:02] [claude-sdk] {"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_011CdCJaUFxkNTpgAdcujQ75","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! That calendar was very rich. Now I have a comprehensive picture. Here's what I've gathered from LexHam's site:\n\n---\n\n## What I Found on LexHam.org\n\n### **Programs (from calendar, search snippets, and page fragments)**\n\n| Program | Details |\n|---|---|\n| **Under the Bridge Concert Series** | Free evening concerts (6–8 PM) at the Hamline bridge / Tot Lot area. Multiple dates through summer. Food trucks, family-friendly, playground access. |\n| **Ice Cream Social** | Annual summer gathering at the Hague Tot Lot — music, bingo, water balloon toss, face painting, crafts. Suggested donation ~$5 adult / $3 child. |\n| **Spaghetti Dinner** | Pay-what-you-can fundraiser (~$10 adult / $5 child) at Dunning Rec Center. |\n| **Movie in the Park** | Free outdoor film screening at Midway Peace Park (e.g., Disney's *Coco*). |\n| **Yoga in the Park** | Free Saturday morning sessions at Midway Peace Park. |\n| **Spring Scavenger Hunt** | Family activity at the Tot Lot, tiered difficulty for ages 2–12. |\n| **Spring Clean Up** | Neighborhood litter pickup coordinated with the City and Friends of Midway Peace Park. |\n| **Portland Ave 4th of July Parade & Social** | Annual neighborhood parade (40+ years running), 10 AM start. |\n| **Community Gardens** (×3) | Dunning Garden (Griggs & Concordia), Lex-Ham Garden (Marshall Ave), Eleanor Graham Garden (Ayd Mill/Hamline/Ashland triangle). |\n| **Blood Drive** | American Red Cross drive hosted at a local church. |\n| **Community Conversations** | Periodic neighborhood discussion forums. |\n\n### **Get Involved / Volunteer Opportunities**\n\n| Role / Opportunity | Details |\n|---|---|\n| **Block Leaders** | Each block has a leader who distributes flyers, shares info, organizes National Night Out, and plans block get-togethers year-round. |\n| **Welcome Wagon** | Volunteers deliver welcome gift bags to new neighbors. |\n| **Crime & Safety Committee** | Meets 3rd Monday of each month, 3:30 PM at Yellowbird Coffee Bar. |\n| **Board of Directors** | 9-member board with co-presidents, co-VPs, treasurer, secretary, and business liaison. Meets monthly at Yellowbird Coffee Bar. |\n| **Social Media Volunteers** | Monitor LHCC social media accounts. |\n| **Community Garden Volunteers** | Participate in the three neighborhood gardens. |\n\n### **Resources**\n\n| Resource | Details |\n|---|---|\n| City of Saint Paul services | Western Police District, Citizen Service Line, recycling, composting, parking, biking, walking, scooters |\n| Aging In Place resources | Local support for residents choosing to age at home |\n| Housing resources | MN Housing, tenant rights (AG handbook), housing counseling, problem properties reporting |\n| Buy Nothing Group | Hyper-local Facebook gift economy group |\n| Lex-Ham Community Arts | Local theatre and music org |\n| Safety links | Crime reporting, incident forms, neighborhood safety |\n\n---\n\n### **Key Patterns Worth Adopting for MNA**\n\nThe things that jump out as directly portable to your documentation:\n\n1. **Block Leader Network** — Very similar to your \"Router\" role, but LexHam formalizes it as a neighborhood-wide network with flyer distribution duties, National Night Out coordination, and year-round block engagement.\n2. **Recurring Signature Events** — They have a calendar of named, annual traditions (Concert Series, Ice Cream Social, Spaghetti Dinner, Parade, Movie Night) that give the neighborhood a rhythm.\n3. **Community Gardens** — A standing program with named, mapped locations.\n4. **Welcome Wagon** — A structured new-neighbor onboarding program.\n5. **Crime & Safety Committee** — A recurring monthly meeting with a fixed schedule and location.\n6. **Yoga / Wellness programming** — Free, low-overhead park events.\n7. **Spring Clean Up** — City-partnered neighborhood cleanup day.\n\nI'm ready to start building these concepts into your MNA documentation. What would you like to tackle first — should we start with a **Programs playbook** (modeled on their event calendar), expand the **block community network** (formalizing the block leader/Router system like their Block Leaders model), or both at once?\n\nSources:\n- [LHCC Programs](https://www.lexham.org/lhccprograms)\n- [LHCC Calendar](https://www.lexham.org/calendar)\n- [LHCC About Us](https://www.lexham.org/about)\n- [LHCC Get Involved](https://www.lexham.org/get-involved)\n- [LHCC Resources](https://www.lexham.org/community-resouces)\n- [LHCC Board of Directors](https://www.lexham.org/board)"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1068,"cache_read_input_tokens":35206,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1068},"output_tokens":4,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"393aa51d-281a-4b41-acea-1abc9b5cff0a","uuid":"9e7ba3fa-1b24-4511-adb6-6a8c26e5028d"}
