[2026-07-19 18:48:07] [claude-sdk] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_012qX8Fy3nh1ZvzN6B46XxTX","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /c/Users/donno/source/mneighbor-alliance/NEIGHBOR_LINK_ONBOARDING.md has been updated successfully. (file state is current in your context — no need to Read it back)"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"393aa51d-281a-4b41-acea-1abc9b5cff0a","uuid":"36cc2ff7-b3e5-4b76-889b-2be100f0c86b","timestamp":"2026-07-19T23:48:07.981Z","tool_use_result":{"filePath":"/c/Users/donno/source/mneighbor-alliance/NEIGHBOR_LINK_ONBOARDING.md","oldString":"### Step 2: Nominate the 3-Person Stewardship Team\nTo keep administration lean and avoid top-heavy boards, each Link is anchored by three specific resident volunteer roles:\n* **The Router (Communications):** Manages local messaging channels, digital invites, porch-to-porch welcome outreach, and cross-neighborhood promotion for [Community Clubs](file:///c:/Users/donno/source/mneighbor-alliance/COMMUNITY_CLUBS.md).\n* **The Ledger (Finance):** Manages the local micro-pool of funds, tracks neighborhood contributions, and coordinates reimbursements.\n* **The Protocol (Logistics):** Holds the master copy of the permitting guide, builds the maps, and coordinates the city insurance certificates.","newString":"### Step 2: Nominate the 3-Person Stewardship Team\nTo keep administration lean and avoid top-heavy boards, each Link is anchored by three specific resident volunteer roles:\n* **The Router (Communications):** Manages local messaging channels, digital invites, porch-to-porch welcome outreach, and cross-neighborhood promotion for [Community Clubs](COMMUNITY_CLUBS.md). Once the Link is active, the Router also recruits and coordinates per-block **Block Leaders** — see the [Block Community Network Playbook](BLOCK_NETWORK.md) for the full model.\n* **The Ledger (Finance):** Manages the local micro-pool of funds, tracks neighborhood contributions, and coordinates reimbursements.\n* **The Protocol (Logistics):** Holds the master copy of the permitting guide, builds the maps, and coordinates the city insurance certificates.","originalFile":"# Standard Operating Procedure for New Chapter Activation\n*This guide is a repeatable deployment script. Whenever a new hyper-local sector wants to join the alliance, the local organizers execute these four steps to spin up an autonomous node under the master legal shield.*\n\n> **Activation Pipeline:** [Define Boundary] --> [Select 3-Person Team] --> [Board Resolution] --> [Deploy Sub-Ledger]\n\n### Step 1: Define the Hyper-Local Boundary\nThe incoming \"Link\" must be defined entirely by its residents. The recommended scale is one central block (the section between the two closest cross streets) plus 2 to 4 immediately adjacent blocks (a 3-to-5-block cluster). This keeps the psychological footprint small, hyper-local, and highly manageable.\n\n### Step 2: Nominate the 3-Person Stewardship Team\nTo keep administration lean and avoid top-heavy boards, each Link is anchored by three specific resident volunteer roles:\n* **The Router (Communications):** Manages local messaging channels, digital invites, porch-to-porch welcome outreach, and cross-neighborhood promotion for [Community Clubs](file:///c:/Users/donno/source/mneighbor-alliance/COMMUNITY_CLUBS.md).\n* **The Ledger (Finance):** Manages the local micro-pool of funds, tracks neighborhood contributions, and coordinates reimbursements.\n* **The Protocol (Logistics):** Holds the master copy of the permitting guide, builds the maps, and coordinates the city insurance certificates.\n\n### Step 3: Execute the Board Charter Resolution\nThe new neighborhood does not file paperwork with the government. Instead, the master MNeighbor Alliance board passes a single-sentence corporate resolution:\n> *\"The board officially recognizes and establishes the '[Neighborhood Name] Link' as an official internal chapter of MNeighbor Alliance, granting it full access to the corporate liability shield, master insurance coverage, and open-source toolkits.\"*\n\n### Step 4: Configure the Sub-Ledger\nThe master MNA bank account remains a single repository, but the master treasurer configures an isolated tracking sub-ledger for the new Link. All funds contributed by neighbors within that specific boundary are tagged exclusively for their local events.\n\n---\n\n### 🌐 The Track B Alternative: The Affiliate MOU\nIf an adjacent neighborhood block is already hyper-organized and possesses its own independent non-profit status (e.g., a localized community council like LexHam), do not use the steps above. Instead, execute the Affiliate Memorandum of Understanding (MOU):\n* **Fiduciary Firebreak:** The MOU explicitly dictates that both organizations remain entirely independent legal entities. Neither assumes financial or legal liability for the actions, debts, or omissions of the other.\n* **Asset Interoperability:** Both groups agree to cross-promote events, coordinate street-closure calendars to avoid scheduling conflicts, and share non-monetary physical assets (e.g., traffic sawhorses, canopies, or tech gear).\n* **The Mesh Council:** The affiliate group appoints one volunteer \"Router\" to sit on a bi-annual peer-to-peer roundtable to maintain an open communication mesh across neighborhoods, including cross-promoting interest groups and community clubs.\n\n> 📝 **Template Filling Note:** When utilizing templates located within the `/templates` folder (such as the Affiliate MOU), ensure all localized variables inside brackets `[ ]` are modified to reflect your node configuration details prior to routing or formal signatures.\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":8,"oldLines":7,"newStart":8,"newLines":7,"lines":[" "," ### Step 2: Nominate the 3-Person Stewardship Team"," To keep administration lean and avoid top-heavy boards, each Link is anchored by three specific resident volunteer roles:","-* **The Router (Communications):** Manages local messaging channels, digital invites, porch-to-porch welcome outreach, and cross-neighborhood promotion for [Community Clubs](file:///c:/Users/donno/source/mneighbor-alliance/COMMUNITY_CLUBS.md).","+* **The Router (Communications):** Manages local messaging channels, digital invites, porch-to-porch welcome outreach, and cross-neighborhood promotion for [Community Clubs](COMMUNITY_CLUBS.md). Once the Link is active, the Router also recruits and coordinates per-block **Block Leaders** — see the [Block Community Network Playbook](BLOCK_NETWORK.md) for the full model."," * **The Ledger (Finance):** Manages the local micro-pool of funds, tracks neighborhood contributions, and coordinates reimbursements."," * **The Protocol (Logistics):** Holds the master copy of the permitting guide, builds the maps, and coordinates the city insurance certificates."," "]}],"userModified":false,"replaceAll":false}}
