[2026-07-19 18:48:46] [SSE-393aa51d-281a-4b41-acea-1abc9b5cff0a]: {"type":"result","success":true,"text":"Here's a summary of everything I just built out:\n\n---\n\n### What Was Created\n\n**New file: `BLOCK_NETWORK.md`** — The full Block Community Network playbook, containing:\n\n1. **Tiered Leadership Model** — The Router remains the Link-wide coordinator, but now recruits and manages per-block **Block Leaders** underneath. Includes an ASCII diagram of the hierarchy.\n\n2. **Block Leader Role Definition** — A table of five core duties (flyer drops, welcome visits, National Night Out, seasonal check-ins, signal relay) with cadence and descriptions. Also explicitly defines what the role is *not* (not a decision-maker, not permanent, not on-call).\n\n3. **Welcome Visit Program** — Lightweight new-neighbor onboarding: a porch visit within 2 weeks of move-in with a single-page info sheet (front: block leader contact, Signal QR, next event; back: city services, safety committee info, reporting numbers).\n\n4. **Crime & Safety Committee** — Standing monthly meeting with a fixed agenda template covering block-by-block check-ins, city/police updates, open discussion, and action items. Includes a legal guardrail warning that the committee is a communication forum, not an enforcement body.\n\n5. **Year-Round Engagement Calendar** — Season-by-season suggested activities from Spring Clean-Up through winter mutual aid, with effort levels marked so Block Leaders can pick what works for their block.\n\n6. **Recruiting Guide** — A conversational recruitment script for the Router and a vacancy protocol for uncovered blocks.\n\n7. **Cross-Reference Table** — Maps how Block Network relates to the Onboarding SOP, Event Playbook, Community Clubs, and Affiliate MOU.\n\n**New template: `templates/WELCOME_INFO_SHEET.md`** — A fillable front-and-back welcome sheet for Block Leaders to customize and print.\n\n**Updated files:**\n- **`README.md`** — Added a new \"Block Community Network\" section with a link to the playbook, positioned before the Community Clubs section.\n- **`NEIGHBOR_LINK_ONBOARDING.md`** — Updated the Router role description to reference Block Leader recruitment and link to the new playbook.\n\n---\n\nWant to move on to building out the **programs calendar** next (formalizing recurring events like LexHam's concert series, ice cream social, spaghetti dinner, etc.)?","sessionId":"393aa51d-281a-4b41-acea-1abc9b5cff0a","costUsd":0.33733675,"provider":"claude","turns":6,"durationMs":229460,"inputTokens":8,"outputTokens":6713}
