, I found information about the streets and neighborhoods you're asking about, but the results don't contain specific GPS coordinates for the intersections. However, I can provide you with the geographic context:\n\nSt. Paul's Rondo neighborhood ran roughly between University Avenue to the north, Selby Avenue to the south, Rice Street to the east, and Lexington Avenue to the west. Four bridges over I-94 connect the two halves of what had been Rondo neighborhood: Lexington Avenue, at the western boundary of Rondo; Victoria Avenue; Dale Avenue; and Western Avenue, close to its eastern boundary.\n\nThe search results confirm that these streets (Selby, Victoria, Lexington, Dale, Summit, Rondo) exist and intersect in the Saint Paul area, but don't provide the exact GPS coordinates you're looking for. To get precise intersection coordinates, you might want to use:\n- Google Maps or mapping applications where you can search for specific intersections\n- The City of Saint Paul's GIS mapping resources\n- Official property/surveying databases that maintain coordinate information\n\nWould you like me to search for more specific information about any particular intersection?\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}}
