[2026-07-19 18:54:49] [claude-sdk] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01FBX9zfpS9VvN8EVRzrvQet","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"\"Rondo frontage road\" Saint Paul MN map I-94\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Rondo Neighborhood | Saint Paul Historical\",\"url\":\"https://saintpaulhistorical.com/items/show/160\"},{\"title\":\"Overview - Rondo Neighborhood & I-94 - LibGuides at Minnesota Historical Society Library\",\"url\":\"https://libguides.mnhs.org/rondo\"},{\"title\":\"Rondo Avenue Renaming | Saint Paul Minnesota\",\"url\":\"https://www.stpaul.gov/projects/public-works/pw2024rondoaverenaming\"},{\"title\":\"Before it was cut in half by I-94, St. Paul’s Rondo was a thriving African-American cultural center - MinnPost\",\"url\":\"https://www.minnpost.com/mnopedia/2017/06/it-was-cut-half-i-94-st-paul-s-rondo-was-thriving-african-american-cultural-center/\"},{\"title\":\"Rondo neighborhood - Wikipedia\",\"url\":\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rondo_neighborhood\"},{\"title\":\"Twin Cities: Rondo Neighborhood & I-94 - Anti-Black Racism - Course and Subject Guides at Saint Mary's University MN\",\"url\":\"https://libguides.smumn.edu/antiracism-blackamericans/twin-cities-rondo\"},{\"title\":\"Why was I-94 built right through the middle of St. Paul's Rondo neighborhood?\",\"url\":\"https://www2.startribune.com/why-did-i-94-get-built-right-through-the-middle-of-st-pauls-rondo-neighborhood/600001544/\"},{\"title\":\"I-94 in the Union Park District: A History of Prioritizing Speed Over Community - Streets.mn\",\"url\":\"https://streets.mn/2022/12/13/i-94-in-union-park/\"},{\"title\":\"Rethinking I-94 — Minneapolis to St. Paul | Let's Talk Transportation - MnDOT\",\"url\":\"https://talk.dot.state.mn.us/rethinking-i94\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here's what I found about the Rondo frontage road near I-94 in Saint Paul, MN:\n\n## Key Information\n\nPart of the original street is now the frontage road near the Best Western Kelly Inn. This frontage road represents what remains of the historic Rondo Avenue after the construction of Interstate 94.\n\nMost of the original Rondo Avenue and much of the historic Rondo neighborhood were destroyed when Interstate 94 was built. Construction of Interstate-94 (I-94) between 1956 and 1968 cut the neighborhood in half and fractured its identity as a cultural center.\n\n## Recent Name Changes\n\nIn January 1964, a resolution was introduced to rename the southern frontage road of the newly constructed interstate to Concordia Avenue. After no public discussion, the resolution passed. However, Concordia Avenue from Griggs Street to Mackubin Street will be renamed Rondo Avenue as part of recent efforts to restore the historic Rondo name to the area.\n\n## Historical Context\n\nSt. Paul's Rondo neighborhood ran roughly between University Avenue to the north, Selby Avenue to the south, Rice Street to the east, and Lexington Avenue to the west. The construction of I-94 had devastating impacts on the community, with more than 600 African American families lost their homes.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"393aa51d-281a-4b41-acea-1abc9b5cff0a","uuid":"50ec9c05-5ca9-4336-99f7-4780111faa24","timestamp":"2026-07-19T23:54:49.264Z","tool_use_result":{"query":"\"Rondo frontage road\" Saint Paul MN map I-94","results":[{"tool_use_id":"srvtoolu_016uH1Zu52sXcmhEKTF7Ac7r","content":[{"title":"Rondo Neighborhood | Saint Paul Historical","url":"https://saintpaulhistorical.com/items/show/160"},{"title":"Overview - Rondo Neighborhood & I-94 - LibGuides at Minnesota Historical Society Library","url":"https://libguides.mnhs.org/rondo"},{"title":"Rondo Avenue Renaming | Saint Paul Minnesota","url":"https://www.stpaul.gov/projects/public-works/pw2024rondoaverenaming"},{"title":"Before it was cut in half by I-94, St. Paul’s Rondo was a thriving African-American cultural center - MinnPost","url":"https://www.minnpost.com/mnopedia/2017/06/it-was-cut-half-i-94-st-paul-s-rondo-was-thriving-african-american-cultural-center/"},{"title":"Rondo neighborhood - Wikipedia","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rondo_neighborhood"},{"title":"Twin Cities: Rondo Neighborhood & I-94 - Anti-Black Racism - Course and Subject Guides at Saint Mary's University MN","url":"https://libguides.smumn.edu/antiracism-blackamericans/twin-cities-rondo"},{"title":"Why was I-94 built right through the middle of St. Paul's Rondo neighborhood?","url":"https://www2.startribune.com/why-did-i-94-get-built-right-through-the-middle-of-st-pauls-rondo-neighborhood/600001544/"},{"title":"I-94 in the Union Park District: A History of Prioritizing Speed Over Community - Streets.mn","url":"https://streets.mn/2022/12/13/i-94-in-union-park/"},{"title":"Rethinking I-94 — Minneapolis to St. Paul | Let's Talk Transportation - MnDOT","url":"https://talk.dot.state.mn.us/rethinking-i94"}]},"Based on the search results, here's what I found about the Rondo frontage road near I-94 in Saint Paul, MN:\n\n## Key Information\n\nPart of the original street is now the frontage road near the Best Western Kelly Inn. This frontage road represents what remains of the historic Rondo Avenue after the construction of Interstate 94.\n\nMost of the original Rondo Avenue and much of the historic Rondo neighborhood were destroyed when Interstate 94 was built. Construction of Interstate-94 (I-94) between 1956 and 1968 cut the neighborhood in half and fractured its identity as a cultural center.\n\n## Recent Name Changes\n\nIn January 1964, a resolution was introduced to rename the southern frontage road of the newly constructed interstate to Concordia Avenue. After no public discussion, the resolution passed. However, Concordia Avenue from Griggs Street to Mackubin Street will be renamed Rondo Avenue as part of recent efforts to restore the historic Rondo name to the area.\n\n## Historical Context\n\nSt. Paul's Rondo neighborhood ran roughly between University Avenue to the north, Selby Avenue to the south, Rice Street to the east, and Lexington Avenue to the west. The construction of I-94 had devastating impacts on the community, with more than 600 African American families lost their homes."],"durationSeconds":6.893028200000001,"searchCount":1}}
[2026-07-19 18:54:49] [SSE-393aa51d-281a-4b41-acea-1abc9b5cff0a]: {"type":"tool_end","name":"WebSearch","toolId":"toolu_01FBX9zfpS9VvN8EVRzrvQet","summary":"Search \"\"Rondo frontage road\" Saint Pa...\"","detail":{"input":{"query":"\"Rondo frontage road\" Saint Paul MN map I-94"},"output":"Web search results for query: \"\"Rondo frontage road\" Saint Paul MN map I-94\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Rondo Neighborhood | Saint Paul Historical\",\"url\":\"https://saintpaulhistorical.com/items/show/160\"},{\"title\":\"Overview - Rondo Neighborhood & I-94 - LibGuides at Minnesota Historical Society Library\",\"url\":\"https://libguides.mnhs.org/rondo\"},{\"title\":\"Rondo Avenue Renaming | Saint Paul Minnesota\",\"url\":\"https://www.stpaul.gov/projects/public-works/pw2024rondoaverenaming\"},{\"title\":\"Before it was cut in half by I-94, St. Paul’s Rondo was a thriving African-American cultural center - MinnPost\",\"url\":\"https://www.minnpost.com/mnopedia/2017/06/it-was-cut-half-i-94-st-paul-s-rondo-was-thriving-african-american-cultural-center/\"},{\"title\":\"Rondo neighborhood - Wikipedia\",\"url\":\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rondo_neighborhood\"},{\"title\":\"Twin Cities: Rondo Neighborhood & I-94 - Anti-Black Racism - Course and Subject Guides at Saint Mary's University MN\",\"url\":\"https://libguides.smumn.edu/antiracism-blackamericans/twin-cities-rondo\"},{\"title\":\"Why was I-94 built right through the middle of St. Paul's Rondo neighborhood?\",\"url\":\"https://www2.startribune.com/why-did-i-94-get-built-right-through-the-middle-of-st-pauls-rondo-neighborhood/600001544/\"},{\"title\":\"I-94 in the Union Park District: A History of Prioritizing Speed Over Community - Streets.mn\",\"url\":\"https://streets.mn/2022/12/13/i-94-in-union-park/\"},{\"title\":\"Rethinking I-94 — Minneapolis to St. Paul | Let's Talk Transportation - MnDOT\",\"url\":\"https://talk.dot.state.mn.us/rethinking-i94\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here's what I found about the Rondo frontage road near I-94 in Saint Paul, MN:\n\n## Key Information\n\nPart of the original street is now the frontage road near the Best Western Kelly Inn. This frontage road represents what remains of the historic Rondo Avenue after the construction of Interstate 94.\n\nMost of the original Rondo Avenue and much of the historic Rondo neighborhood were destroyed when Interstate 94 was built. Construction of Interstate-94 (I-94) between 1956 and 1968 cut the neighborhood in half and fractured its identity as a cultural center.\n\n## Recent Name Changes\n\nIn January 1964, a resolution was introduced to rename the southern frontage road of the newly constructed interstate to Concordia Avenue. After no public discussion, the resolution passed. However, Concordia Avenue from Griggs Street to Mackubin Street will be renamed Rondo Avenue as part of recent efforts to restore the historic Rondo name to the area.\n\n## Historical Context\n\nSt. Paul's Rondo neighborhood ran roughly between University Avenue to the north, Selby Avenue to the south, Rice Street to the east, and Lexington Avenue to the west. The construction of I-94 had devastating impacts on the community, with more than 600 African American families lost their homes.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}}
